---
// Privacy Policy for istefox.dev and the Agentwake app, under the GDPR (Regulation (EU)
// 2016/679) and the Italian Privacy Code (D.lgs. 196/2003 as amended by D.lgs. 101/2018).
// The processing inventory below is sourced from the repo itself: beta signups in
// functions/api/waitlist.ts (Cloudflare KV + Turnstile + Resend), purchases via Polar,
// downloads from GitHub Releases, Sparkle update checks, and the theme/banner storage keys.
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';

const LAST_UPDATED = '23 July 2026';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead
			title={`Privacy Policy — ${SITE_TITLE}`}
			description="How istefox.dev and Agentwake handle personal data under the GDPR: what is collected, why, who processes it, and your rights."
		/>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main class="legal">
			<h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
			<p class="updated">Last updated: {LAST_UPDATED}</p>

			<p>
				This policy explains how personal data is handled on istefox.dev and in the Agentwake
				macOS app, under Regulation (EU) 2016/679 (GDPR) and the Italian Privacy Code
				(Legislative Decree 196/2003, as amended). The short version: the site collects your
				email only if you sign up for the Agentwake beta, the app itself sends no telemetry, and
				nothing is sold or shared for advertising.
			</p>

			<h2>1. Data controller</h2>
			<p>
				Stefano Ferri, independent software developer, Italy. Contact:
				<a href="mailto:stefferri@icloud.com">stefferri@icloud.com</a>.
			</p>

			<h2>2. What is processed, and why</h2>

			<h3>Beta signup</h3>
			<p>
				If you join the Agentwake beta, I process your email address, together with the browser
				user-agent and referring page of the signup request. The email is used to send you the
				beta invite (download link and Pro activation link) and, sparingly, beta-related
				communications; there is no newsletter. Legal basis: performance of the beta agreement
				you request when you sign up (art. 6(1)(b) GDPR). The data is stored in Cloudflare
				Workers KV.
			</p>

			<h3>Anti-abuse check</h3>
			<p>
				Cloudflare Turnstile protects the signup form by analysing technical signals from your
				browser to tell humans from bots. Legal basis: legitimate interest in preventing spam
				and abuse (art. 6(1)(f) GDPR).
			</p>

			<h3>Hosting and connection logs</h3>
			<p>
				Cloudflare Pages hosts the site. Like any host, Cloudflare processes connection data
				(IP address, request metadata) to deliver the site and protect it from attacks. Legal
				basis: legitimate interest in operating and securing the site (art. 6(1)(f) GDPR).
			</p>

			<h3>Transactional email</h3>
			<p>
				Resend delivers the beta invite email, and processes your email address on my behalf
				solely to deliver that message.
			</p>

			<h3>Purchases</h3>
			<p>
				Polar Software Inc. operates the checkout for Agentwake Pro as merchant of record.
				Polar collects and processes the data needed for the purchase (name, email, payment and
				billing details, invoicing) as an independent controller, under its own privacy policy. I
				receive from Polar the order information needed to support you (such as your email and
				order reference), never your full payment details.
			</p>

			<h3>Downloads</h3>
			<p>
				GitHub Releases serves the Agentwake DMG download; GitHub processes connection data for
				that download under its own privacy policy.
			</p>

			<h2>3. The Agentwake app</h2>
			<p>
				Agentwake contains no telemetry and no analytics. The only network calls the app makes
				are Sparkle update checks against the release feed, license key validation with Polar,
				and the pricing-table refresh you trigger yourself. The optional token-cost estimate
				reads usage fields from local Claude Code session files, only after you opt in, and the
				data never leaves your Mac. Agent hooks report only "this session is alive" heartbeats,
				locally.
			</p>

			<h2>4. Cookies and local storage</h2>
			<p>
				The site sets no advertising or analytics cookies and uses no tracking. It stores two
				technical preferences in your browser: your light/dark theme choice (localStorage) and
				the dismissal of the price banner (sessionStorage). Cloudflare Turnstile may set its own
				strictly functional cookie while verifying the signup form. None of this requires a
				cookie banner under the Garante's guidelines on technical cookies.
			</p>

			<h2>5. Recipients and processors</h2>
			<p>The services that touch personal data, each bound by its own data processing terms:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Cloudflare, Inc. (hosting, KV storage, Turnstile)</li>
				<li>Resend (Plus Five Five, Inc.) (transactional email delivery)</li>
				<li>Polar Software Inc. (checkout, as independent merchant of record)</li>
				<li>GitHub, Inc. (DMG downloads, release feed, issue tracker if you open an issue)</li>
			</ul>
			<p>No data is sold, rented, or shared for advertising purposes.</p>

			<h2>6. Transfers outside the EEA</h2>
			<p>
				The providers above are US companies, so data may be processed in the United States.
				Transfers rely on the EU-US Data Privacy Framework where the provider is certified, or
				on Standard Contractual Clauses, in line with Chapter V of the GDPR.
			</p>

			<h2>7. Retention</h2>
			<p>
				I keep beta signup data for the duration of the beta program and the launch that
				follows, then delete it, or sooner if you ask. Hosting and security logs follow
				Cloudflare's short technical retention. Polar keeps purchase records for as long as tax
				law requires.
			</p>

			<h2>8. Your rights</h2>
			<p>
				Under articles 15 to 22 of the GDPR you can ask for access to your data, a copy of it,
				rectification, deletion, restriction of processing, portability, and you can object to
				processing based on legitimate interest. Just write to
				<a href="mailto:stefferri@icloud.com">stefferri@icloud.com</a>; I answer within the
				timeframes the GDPR sets. You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Italian
				supervisory authority, the
				<a href="https://www.garanteprivacy.it" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"
					>Garante per la Protezione dei Dati Personali</a
				>.
			</p>

			<h2>9. No profiling</h2>
			<p>
				No automated decision-making and no profiling take place, on the site or in the app.
			</p>

			<h2>10. Changes to this policy</h2>
			<p>
				If the processing changes (for example, a new provider), I update this page and the date
				at the top. Substantial changes affecting beta testers get announced by email.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>

<style>
	.legal h1 {
		margin-bottom: 0.2em;
	}
	.updated {
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		font-size: 0.95em;
		margin-bottom: 2em;
	}
	.legal h2 {
		margin-top: 1.6em;
		font-size: 1.25em;
	}
	.legal h3 {
		margin-top: 1.1em;
		font-size: 1.05em;
	}
</style>
